Q.8) write a program to check if number is odd or even.

ans:-// for even -->1
       // for odd -->0
#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>

int main() {
    int x;
    printf("enter a number : ");
    scanf("%d" , &x);
    
    printf("%d", x % 2 == 0);
    
    return 0;
}

explaination:-

//                                  -for a statement(will not include in output)
#include <math.h>    -to code easier for mathematical           
                                      operations  
int                                 -to define a variable 
scanf                           -to take input
%d                                -defines that side is intiger
&                                   -shows the location of variable 

(note:- in output, it will print 0 for odd number and 1 for even number)
